<div id='gazette_story'>
    <div align='center'>
        <font size='4'><b>Help Wanted</b></font><br>
                                <img src='http://graphics.millsberry.com/site_gfx/interiors/gazette/gazette_20100610.jpg' border='1' width='280' height='200'>
                        </div>
        <div id='gazette_byline'><em>By Audrey Smythe-Wei<br>Editor-in-Chief</em></div>
        <b>Thursday, June 10, 2010</b> &mdash;
    Looking to make some extra Millsbucks? Hoping to play ball like a pro? Or make clothes like Loretta Rivers from the Wearhouse? Well, now you can-plus get paid for it! Yep, you heard it here first: Big things are happening in Millsberry, starting from a new location<a href="http://millsberry.com/career_center"><i>-the Career Center!</i></a><br><br>Popping up right next to the Clothing Store and replacing the Recording Studio, the <a href="http://millsberry.com/career_center"><i>Career Center</i></a> is a little ray of sunshine, downtown. And, to kick off the grand opening, there&#039;s a new-to-town Millsberrian running the show: Caroline Carrera!<br><br>&quot;I&#039;ve had this business for years and decided it&#039;d be great to bring it to Millsberry. Simply <a href="http://millsberry.com/career_center"><i>swing on by</i></a> and I&#039;ll tell you what positions are open! Yesterday, for example, a job-seeking resident came in and found work as a <a href="http://millsberry.com/career_center"><i>writer</i></a>. One of his tasks was to read up on a slightly more famous writer: Zora Neale Hurston. After he finished reading the book from the bookstore, he got a Millscheck...plus some cool writing tools of his own. He also got a promotion, so his next project will be to score 400 points playing Solver.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Right now,&quot; Caroline continued, &quot;there are only a few careers to choose from but, in the coming weeks, there&#039;ll be new and exciting jobs popping up all over. And more jobs means more Millschecks--and more cool items--for you to bring home!&quot;<br><br>Intrigued by the possibilities, we asked Caroline to tell us about some of the other positions available now. She noted, &quot;Everyone is excited about the <a href="http://millsberry.com/career_center"><i>fashion designer job</i></a>--available because Loretta&#039;s Wearhouse fashions have been in such high demand! Apparently, she needs all the help she can get, so your first task might be to design something like a super cool tank-top.<br>After that, you might have to make a bigger garment, like a button-down shirt. But just to be clear: you can&#039;t start more than one job in one day. So, if you start working as a <a href="http://millsberry.com/career_center"><i>police officer</i></a>, you can&#039;t choose to work for Loretta on the same day. Instead, simply come back the next day and either start on your next police officer task, or start a completely new job, be it as a designer or<br>whatever!&quot;<br><br>We&#039;re also pretty confident that another new career choice will be that of a surfer. How did we discover this? We saw residents wearing wet suits all around town!<br><br>So head on over to the <a href="http://millsberry.com/career_center"><i>Career Center</i></a> to meet Caroline and pick a job, come back the next day to get going on your new task--and get movin&#039; toward some Millschecks and cool prizes!
    </div>

